data.text:
The Supreme Law

Maeterlinck, Maurice; K.S. Shelvankar [Translator]

New York: E.P. Dutton & Company, 1935.

First American edition. 160 pp. Bound in publisher's orange cloth with dark navy lettering. Fine in Very Good dust jacket, rubbed, small chip at head. The Belgian Nobel laureate (mainly for his dramatic works) takes on physics, defending Newton and criticizing Einstein. Uncommon in jacket. Item #140943527
